As per [https://atlaseye.atlassian.com/cru/CR-BAM-3435#c61904].
We're currently using
{{File planSourceDirectory = BuildContextHelper.getBuildWorkingDirectory(buildContext)}}
instead of 
{{File planSourceDirectory = buildContext.getBuildDefinition().getRepositoryV2().getSourceCodeDirectory(buildContext.getPlanKey())}}

We need to ensure the method for getting the build workind directory is documented on CAC (especially in the "changes for Bamboo 3.3") - as we needed to update some of the 3rd party plugins, so probably plugin developers will encounter this problem too.

When using a dialog box to update something, we need to refresh the page in order to display its updated contents. Every time we have to do this we are adding approximately the following code to the .ftl file 

{noformat}
<script type="text/javascript">
    var updateBuildRquirement = function (data) {
        window.location.reload(true);
    };
</script>
{noformat}

We do this a lot, is there some way to default this behaviour without having to inline it all the time?

JB : Ideally we wouldn't be doing this, we'd be updating the page inline instead of refreshing the page - which would require custom coding just about every time.
Will see if we can come up with something more ideal however (such as if a submitCallback isn't specified we default to refreshing the page, or something like that).
